Description:   The Investor Services Senior Director will have senior-level business oversight over the full-service sub-accounting and cash portal operations within PFPCs Shareholder Services Operations organization.  The Senior Director will manage the team that is responsible for all day-to-day full-service sub-accounting services provided by PFPC on the SuRPAS platform.  The Senior Director will also be accountable for the successful implementation of sub-accounting services for new full-service clients converting onto the PFPC sub-accounting platform.  The Senior Director will oversee all workflows and distribution of work across available resources.Working familiarity with mutual fund audit and compliance activities.

Ability to assess risk and create appropriate risk management strategies.  Strong mentoring and staff / manager development skills.  Ability to multitask and work in a fast-paced environment with tight deadlines and turn-around times.  Effective written and verbal communication skills, including formal presentation skills.  Must be comfortable with and have experience interacting with all levels of staff and management at client and prospect institutions.  Ability to support the sales efforts for the business
Strong decision-making ability and technical aptitude.  Seasoned leader with the ability to contribute to overall strategic direction of the group and influence parties and entities not under his/her direct control.

PFPC, a wholly owned subsidiary of the PNC Financial Services Group, is one of the largest full-service mutual fund transfer agent and fund accounting provider in the United States.  You will find an environment where achievements are recognized and rewarded and where the potential for advancement is as limitless as your drive and ambition.

PFPC does not accept unsolicited Agency Resumes.  PFPC will not pay fees to any third party agency or firm that does not have a signed PFPC Agency Fee Agreement.
PNC is an Equal Employment Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer -- M/F/D/V/SO

